        <hl1>On This First Day, a Fanfare for the New Era; Trio for a New World</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Eduardo Gonzalez-Cueva letter says insuring peace in new century will require democratic reform of United Nations, civil society's control of World Trade Organization and creation of international criminal court; drawing</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>After reading Robert D. Kaplan's grim predictions of a re-feudalized and war-ridden 21st century (Op-Ed, Dec. 27), I think there are three urgent lines of action for concerned world citizens: the democratic reform of the United Nations, civil society's control of the World Trade Organization and the immediate creation of an international criminal court.</p>
        <p>EDUARDO GONZALEZ -CUEVA  New York, Dec. 28, 1999</p>
      </block>
